Connect and Reorganize Nodes or Branches in a Batch Data Transform

Connect disconnected nodes or branches to append data from any node to any other node in a batch data transform. You can also create a branch at an intermediate node, and append it to another path in the batch data transform.

To create a branch and join or append it to another path, hover over a node to see the Branch button (). Then drag the Branch button on top of a node in the other path.
In the Connect Nodes box, select to append the data.
To append data to another node, drag the Add Node button () for a node or a Branch button on top of the predecessor.
Then select to append the data in the Connect Nodes box. This canvas joins aggregated account data back to the account records.
To make the flow of data easier to view, reposition the data transform nodes in the canvas. Select and move individual nodes, or drag your mouse to select as many nodes as you want. Pull the group of nodes around to rearrange, or delete them all at once.
For example, you can move upstream nodes after a downstream node in the canvas, where nodes flow right to left.
